(1.) That the ſame individual Thouſand Years, are meant throughout the whole Chapter; as appears from the Greek Article (
                        〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
                     ); whereby, reference is made to each foregoing Thouſand Years, and it is ſhewn that they are the ſame. For Satan is bound a Thouſand Years, Verſe 2. and is reſtrained, Verſe 3. from deceiving the Nations (
                        〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
                     ) during the ſame thouſand Years: The Dead Saints and Martyrs live and Reign with Chriſt (
                        〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
                     ) for the ſame ſpace of Years, Verſe 4. during which alſo, the Wicked are in a ſtate of Death, Verſe 5. The Living Saints are partakers in the firſt Reſurrection, during a Thouſand Years, Verſe 6. at the End of which very Thouſand Years, Satan is looſed, Verſe 7. Whence it will follow, that the Thouſand Years during which


                     Satan was bound, are the ſame with thoſe, during which the Living Saints Reigned with Chriſt; and that they are the ſame with the Thouſand Years aſſigned to the Dead Saints raiſed, and the Dead State of the Wicked; becauſe they which agree in one Third, muſt agree amongſt themſelves.
